Claims Claims 1. A method for 3D modeling of a construction or structure, said method comprising: (a) obtaining digital 2D images of said construction or structure; (b) producing a 3D image from said 2D images of said construction or structure; (c) transforming said 3D image to a data point cloud presentation of said construction or structure; (d) electing a collection of data points from said cloud of data points; (e) identifying an object of said construction or structure that match said collection of data points; (f) attaching corresponding visual images to a record of said identified object; and (g) repeating steps (a)-(f) to any collection of data points in said cloud of data points until constructing a 3D model based on combination of all identified objects. 2. The method of claim 1, wherein said identifying of an object comprises: (a) delimiting said collection of said elected data points to match to said object from a library of objects related to said construction or structure; (b) calculating probability of each data point to relate to said collection of data points that defines said object identified; (c) filtering data points with lesser probability to be related to said object identified; (d) recording a relative spatial position of said object identified in said cloud of points. 3. The method according to claim 2, further comprising: (a) assigning relative coordinates to every data point and locating said data point in space relative to other data points in its vicinity; and (b) assigning metadata such as color and shade to every data point. 4. The method according to claim 2, wherein said filtering further comprises: (a) comparing between data and metadata of neighbor data points; 

 (b) calculating probability of relating said neighbor data points to a single object of said construction or structure; and (c) including said neighbor data points in or rejecting them out of said collection of data points that relate to said object above or below a selected threshold of probability, respectively. 5. The method according to claim 4, wherein said filtering continues dynamically when matching a pattern of an object to said selected collection of data points until proper match is achieved. 6. The method according to claim 1, wherein number of said data points is in the range of 50 to 500 millions. 7. The method according to claim 1, further comprising defect analysis, said defect analysis comprising: (a) characterizing and recording a particular defect examined; (b) identifying said defect and location thereof in an object of said 3D model of said construction or structure; and (c) assigning a grade and attributes to said defect. 8. The method according to claim 7, wherein characterizing and identifying said defect comprises; (a) searching through a defect and defect type dedicated digital library for defects with similar characteristics to those attributed to said defect; (b) comparing said characteristics of said defect and defect type to each other; (c) uploading defects and defect types stored in said dedicated digital library that have characteristics similar to those of said defect; (d) selecting the most similar defect type to said defect; and (e) tagging said defect with an identification code designating said defect type. 9. The method according to claim 8, further comprising: (a) importing historical 3D model or models constructed in previous stages; (b) locating 3D images that correspond to a particular object in said 3D model; 

 (c) displaying visual, actual part in said construction or structure corresponding to said object; (d) accessing historical database of previous surveys for comparing visual and grading data; and (e) systematically guiding a user in a walkthrough approach to identification of said defect. 10. The method according to claim 9, wherein said walkthrough approach comprises: (a) naked-eye, semi- automated or automated defect detection; (b) uploading a library of defect types for the identification of said defect in realtime; and (c) providing a decision support system and quality control procedures for obtaining optimal identification and grading of said defect. 11. The method according to claim 10, wherein said automated defect detection comprises: (a) automated visual scanning of images taken of said construction or structure; (b) pattern matching between suspected defects identified in images of a part of said construction or structure and defects stored in a digital library; (c) performing spatial data point analysis in comparing between current image and historical image(s) of said part of said construction or structure; (d) modeling said part based on said data point analysis; and (e) identifying mismatch between said modeled part according current and historical images and comparing said mismatch to known defect patterns stored in said dedicated defect type library 12. The method according to claim 10, wherein said semi-automated defect detection comprises: (a) providing a user with resulting conclusions of defect identification; (b) providing said user with interface for classifying said defect identification as positive, negative or false-positive identification of said defect; (c) classifying said defect and its severity level; and (d) labeling said defect according to identification. 13. The method according to claim 7, further comprising recommendation for treatment comprising: (a) assigning values to selected parameters that define severity of said defect; (b) weighting said values according to selected weight values assigned for each parameter; (c) weighting and calculating total weighted value and assessing impact of said defect on strength, durability and performance of said construction or structure. 14. The method according to claim 13, further comprising: (a) observing all defects in all objects of said 3D model of said construction or structure; (b) weighting said defects together to obtain total strength, durability and performance of said construction or structure; and (c) producing Critical Condition Performance Index and Average Condition Performance Index for all defects combined for assessing impact of any selected defect of said defects on strength, durability and performance on said construction or structure. 15. The method according to any one of claims 1 to 14, wherein said construction or structure are selected from bridges, highways, roads, railways, pavements, above- and under- ground piping, facilities, plants, buildings and towers. 16. A system for 3D modeling of a construction or structure, said system comprising: (a) remotely operated and controlled light aerial UAV; (b) high-resolution digital photographing means mounted on said UAV; (c) detection devices and orientation geo-location devices mounted on said UAV, said detection devices are configured to locate and identify said construction or structure selected for survey; (d) remote control and data processing unit in communication with said UAV, said remote control and data processing unit are configured to produce flight mission for said UAV and instructions for mapping and grating said construction or structure to be surveyed; 

 (e) digital storing means for storing 2D images of said construction or structure taken by said digital photographing means; (f) digital data processing means for retrieving said stored 2D images and constructing a 3D image of said construction or structure based on said 2D images; (g) means for transforming said 3D image to a cloud of data points; (h) digital library of 3D patterns of typical objects matching parts of said construction or structure; (i) means for matching a pattern of an object of said construction or structure to a selected collection of data points in said cloud of data points; and (j) digital data processing means for constructing a 3D model of said construction or structure based on said matching of 3D objects to said cloud of data points. 17. The system according to claim 16, further comprising an evaluation module for evaluating severity of a defect in said construction or structure, said evaluation module is configured to visually identify said defect in any mode selected from naked-eye, semi-automatic and automatic identification, accumulating information on correspondence between type of a defect and possible visual representation of said defect, providing selected possible types of defects according to said images provided by said visual identification means and providing conclusion of the type of defect to a user. 18. The system according to claim 17, wherein said evaluation module is automatic, wherein said module comprises: (a) a dedicated defect type digital library; (b) a module for pattern matching between suspected defects identified in said images and defects stored in said digital library; (c) spatial analysis functionality for comparing between said images and historical image(s) of a part of said construction or structure that is surveyed; (d) a data point based modeling module configured for analyzing said images, and identifying mismatch between said images upon comparative investigation thereof; 19. The system according to claim 18, wherein said system is a continuously learning system that is configured to record, store and upload user observations for further defect identification assignments and improve performance from a statistical perspective over time. 20. The system according to claim 17, further comprising a recommendation module for recommending treatment following evaluation of said defect, said recommendation module is configured to assign values to selected parameters that define severity of said defect, weighing said values according to selected weight values for each parameter, weighting and calculating total value and assessing impact of said defect on strength, durability and performance of said construction or structure. The system according to claim 20, wherein said recommendation module is configured to accumulate contribution of all defects observed and weight them together to obtain total strength, durability and performance of said construction or structure. 22. The system according to claim 20, wherein said evaluation and recommendation further comprise manufacturing of a grading sheet for said construction or structure, said grading sheet listing said defects identified, severity, quantity and description thereof for every object in said 3D model, said grading sheet further listing images of particular parts of said construction or structure corresponding to particular objects with said list of defects. 23. The system according to claim 16, wherein said detection devices are selected from IR sensors, Lidar, GPS means. 24. The system according to claim 16, wherein said construction or structure are selected from bridges, highways, roads, railways, pavements, above- and underground piping, facilities, plants, buildings and towers.
